<div id="p92" class="blockpost rowodd">
	<h2><span><span class="conr">#7&nbsp;</span><a href="viewtopic.php?pid=92#p92">2008-03-13 13:26:13</a></span></h2>
	<div class="box">
		<div class="inbox">
			<div class="postleft">
				<dl>
					<dt><strong><a href="profile.php?id=89601">dave</a></strong></dt>
					<dd class="usertitle"><strong>Editor</strong></dd>
					<dd class="postavatar"></dd>
				</dl>
			</div>
			<div class="postright">
				<h3> Re: Discussion of BEP 7: IPv6 Tracker Extension</h3>
				<div class="postmsg">
					<p>Teredo does not require the ISP to set up a relay server.&nbsp; Relays are only necessary if the tunnel endpoint does not sit on the destination end system, and they can be provided by customer networks to act as gateways between ipv6 islands and the ipv4 Internet.&nbsp; &nbsp;In the dominant case for home users, the tunnel endpoint is the customer's computer so there is no relay.<br /><br />That said, someone has to run a STUN-like server to set up the tunnel and do NAT hole punching.&nbsp; Thankfully Microsoft does this.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="clearer"></div>
			<div class="postfootleft"><p>Offline</p></div>
			<div class="postfootright"><div>&nbsp;</div></div>
		</div>
	</div>
