				<div class="postmsg">
					<p>&gt; I said it before: It doesn't make sense to limit the peers-key to contain only ipv4 adresses<br /><br />Why not? What is the inherent benefit of using a single key with complicated semantics over two separate keys with very simple semantics?<br /><br />&gt; And that's where I beg to differ: How is an IPv4-only tracker supposed to serve IPv6-only clients, or to check IPv6-entries for connectivity?<br /><br />It uses Teredo for instance</p>
				</div>
